Former Premier League footballer Clarke Carlisle has been pictured for the first time since returning home from hospital following his horror collision with a lorry.

The 35-year-old was snapped looking battered and bruised as he spoke to a reporter outside his house in Yorkshire on Saturday.

Carlisle was released from hospital on Friday six weeks after sustaining life-threatening injuries that left him in a coma.

