Carlisle's wife, Gemma, revealed on Twitter that she was bringing her husband home and thanked fans for their 'amazing support and love'. 

The former Professional Footballers' Association chairman was seriously injured on the A64, near York, on December 22. 

The collision came two days after he was charged with a drink-driving offence of failing to provide a sample.

On Friday, Mrs Carlisle said on Twitter: 'Nearly 6 weeks on... Today I'm collecting Mr C to come home full time! Thanks once again for your amazing support and love. £luckytobehere'

